---
import MainNav from '../../components/MainNav.astro';

const systems = [
  {
    name: "Routing",
    text: "Not every truth belongs in the same room. The house sorts by purpose before it preserves by category.",
  },
  {
    name: "Recursion",
    text: "A return is not a repeat. Each pass should deepen orientation, not trap the seeker in decorative loops.",
  },
  {
    name: "Signal",
    text: "Intensity is not authority. Signal is what remains coherent after heat, fear, and performance fall away.",
  },
  {
    name: "State",
    text: "The room is read before the archive speaks. Condition changes meaning, and meaning changes the hand.",
  },
  {
    name: "Boundary",
    text: "Public, private, sealed, and authored lanes do different work. Crossing them requires intention.",
  },
  {
    name: "Descent",
    text: "The Labyrinth prepares approach. The Black Vault keeps what should not be mistaken for display.",
  },
];
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <title>Operating Systems - Labyrinth</title>
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cinzel:wght@400;600;700&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <style>
      :global(*) {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      :global(body) {
        margin: 0;
        min-height: 100vh;
        background:
          radial-gradient(circle at 72% 18%, rgba(98, 98, 120, 0.1), transparent 34%),
          radial-gradient(circle at 22% 76%, rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.07), transparent 34%),
          #050505;
        color: #aaaab8;
        font-family: "Cinzel", serif;
      }

      .chamber-shell {
        width: min(980px, calc(100% - 2rem));
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 3rem) 0 4rem;
      }

      .chamber {
        padding: clamp(1.5rem, 5vw, 3rem);
        border: 1px solid rgba(154, 154, 170, 0.24);
        border-radius: 10px;
        background: linear-gradient(145deg, rgba(12, 12, 16, 0.88), rgba(5, 5, 5, 0.96));
        box-shadow: 0 0 50px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.75), inset 0 0 50px rgba(154, 154, 170, 0.035);
      }

      .kicker {
        color: rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.72);
        font-size: 0.82rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.18rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        text-align: center;
      }

      h1 {
        margin: 0.8rem 0 1rem;
        color: #c4a76f;
        font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 7vw, 3.6rem);
        letter-spacing: 0.12rem;
        line-height: 1.08;
        text-align: center;
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }

      .lede {
        max-width: 760px;
        margin: 0 auto 2.2rem;
        color: rgba(170, 170, 184, 0.9);
        font-size: 1.05rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .system-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(230px, 1fr));
        gap: 1rem;
        margin: 2rem 0;
      }

      .system-card {
        min-height: 180px;
        padding: 1.1rem;
        border: 1px solid rgba(154, 154, 170, 0.2);
        border-radius: 8px;
        background: rgba(18, 18, 24, 0.56);
      }

      .system-card h2 {
        margin: 0 0 0.7rem;
        color: #d2b982;
        font-size: 1.12rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.08rem;
      }

      .system-card p,
      .closing {
        color: rgba(170, 170, 184, 0.9);
        line-height: 1.7;
      }

      .system-card p {
        margin: 0;
      }

      .closing {
        max-width: 760px;
        margin: 2rem auto 0;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .return-link {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        margin-top: 2rem;
      }

      .return-link a {
        color: #c4a76f;
        text-decoration: none;
        border: 1px solid rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.32);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 0.7rem 1.1rem;
      }

      .return-link a:hover {
        background: rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.1);
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div class="chamber-shell">
      <MainNav />
      <main class="chamber">
        <div class="kicker">Second Chamber</div>
        <h1>Operating Systems</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          Ashvault is not a pile of beautiful pages. It is a house with routing logic.
          The Labyrinth names the systems beneath the rooms so depth can be approached
          without turning everything into archive, performance, or noise.
        </p>

        <section class="system-grid" aria-label="Labyrinth operating systems">
          {
            systems.map((system) => (
              <article class="system-card">
                <h2>{system.name}</h2>
                <p>{system.text}</p>
              </article>
            ))
          }
        </section>

        <p class="closing">
          The house does not mature by adding more doors. It matures when every door
          knows what kind of truth it is allowed to hold.
        </p>

        <nav class="return-link" aria-label="Labyrinth return">
          <a href="/labyrinth">Return to the Labyrinth</a>
        </nav>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
